4b","url":"https://api.github.com/users/frisco82","html_url":"https://github.com/frisco82","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/frisco82/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/frisco82/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/frisco82/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/frisco82/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/frisco82/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/frisco82/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/frisco82/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/frisco82/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/frisco82/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-10-11t15:37:46z","updated_at":"2013-10-11t15:37:46z","body":"@pvince81 the problem on owncloud 5.0.11 was with actions tied to mimetypes that are not the default one.\r\nthe problem was that the mimetype was not set when filelist.addfile was added so only actions with type 'all' where appended, default one is checked when you click on the row and by then the mymetype was as it should.\r\n\r\nthat said your pr should fix this issue too but you can test it running this from the console and then uploading an image:\r\n\r\n```\r\nfileactions.register('image', 'test', oc.permission_read, function () {\r\n\treturn oc.imagepath('core', 'actions/rename');\r\n}, function (filename) {\r\n\talert('test');\r\n});\r\n```"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/26147824","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/4971#issuecomment-26147824","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/4971","id":26147824,"user":{"login":"pvince81","id":277525,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/e446b529679416eb70eafb4ca4da5bbe?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f89d7c394e6dcdf87a91c75ac3b2ccbe8.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"e446b529679416eb70eafb4ca4da5bbe","url":"https://a